<p><font>Cf. Shakespeare, <em>The Merchant of Venice</em>: "Signoir Antonio,
    many a time and oft / In the Rialto you have rated me / about my moneys and my usances: /
    Still I have borne it with a patient shrug" (1.3.101-4)</font>. From his historical
    perspective of his own image as a martyr, this is the one Bleistein selects to complement
    Burbank's perception.</p>
